President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 1 through May 7, 2016, as Public Service Recognition Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of civil servants in ensuring America's democracy runs smoothly and effectively. It recognizes the contributions of civil servants in various sectors such as engineering, education, military service, and social work. The proclamation emphasizes the need for talented and patriotic young people to join the effort of serving their fellow Americans. It also acknowledges the challenges faced by public servants and their commitment to building a better country and bringing lasting change to the lives of ordinary people. The proclamation discusses the initiatives taken by the administration to recruit, uplift, and empower exceptional civil servants, including banning the box on most federal job applications and implementing programs that encourage collaboration. President Obama calls upon all Americans to recognize and appreciate the hard work and dedication of public servants through appropriate activities, events, and programs.